HEADWORD: Superiority
<hw>Su*pe`ri*or"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>sup⟦eacute⟧riorit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, LL.
<ets>superioritas</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality, state, or condition of
being superior; <as>as, <ex>superiority</ex> of rank;
<ex>superiority</ex> in merit.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Preeminence; excellence; predominancy;
prevalence; ascendency; odds; advantage.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Superiorly</ent>⟦br⟧
